.bd
PROGRAM
.in +5
.br
.bd
mkdir
- make directory


.in -5
.bd
USAGE           
.in +5
.br
.bd
mkdir newdir ...


.in -5
.bd
FUNCTION   
.in +5
.br
.bd
Mkdir
creates the specified directory or directories.
Entries for "." and ".." are created automatically.


.in -5
.bd
ERRORS     
.in +5
.br
The given directory names must not yet exist.
.bd
Mkdir
requires write permission on the parent directory.

If a multiple element path name is given, 
.bd
mkdir
creates each of the directories in the path leading to
the desired directory.

It is not possible to remove a directory from the system that 
contains files;  files must first be removed using the 
.bd
rm
command.


.in -5
.bd
EXAMPLES
.in +5
.br
.bd
mkdir /a/sally
.bd
mkdir /usr/spool/mail /usr/spool/lpr


Each directory created is accessible to any user.  It is advisable
to organize your work by keeping related files together in their own,
separate directories (i.e., mkdir programs, mv *.c programs, etc.).


.in -5
.bd
SEE ALSO
.in +5
